<section class="brand--ministry-of-justice brand__border-color organisation__brand-border-top organisation__section-wrap organisation__margin-bottom" id="what-we-do">
  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--padding gem-c-heading--margin-bottom-2  ">What the Criminal Procedure Rule Committee does</h2>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
    
          <p></p>
<div class="govspeak">
<p>The Criminal Procedure Rules govern the way criminal cases are managed, and set out the processes of the criminal courts.</p>

<p>Criminal Procedure Rule Committee is an advisory non-departmental public body, sponsored by the <a class="brand__color" href="/government/organisations/ministry-of-justice">Ministry of Justice</a>.</p>
</div>

          <p>
            <a href="/government/organisations/criminal-procedure-rule-committee/about" class="brand__color">
              Read more about what we do
            </a>
          </p>

</div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>



